1. What is Shadow DOM?
- Shadown DOM is an hidden/encapsulated DOM structure inside an element
- That means:
    - It cannot access it directly like normal DOM
    - It is isolated from the main DOM

- Simple definition
    - Shadow DOM is an hidden mini DOM inside an webpage

2. Why Shadow DOM is used?
- Main purpose:
    - Encapsulation (Isolation of code)
    - Prevent CSS conflicts
    - Build reusable UI components
- Commonly used for :
    - Web components
    - Modern UI frames

3. Real-time Examples
- You already see Shadow DOM in:
    - Date picker
    - Video player controls
    - Chrome DevTools elements
    - Material UI components

4. Structure of Shadow DOM
    <host-element>
    #shadow-root (open)
        <input type="text">
    </host-element>
- Important terms:
    Host element -> Element where Shadow DOM is attached
    Shadow Room -> Entry point of Shadow DOM
    Shadow tree -> Elements inside shadow DOM

5. Types of Shadow DOM
- 1. Open Shadow DOM
    - Can be accessed by using Javascript
        element.shadowRoot

- ❌ 2. Closed Shadow DOM
    - Can not be accessed
        element.shadowRoot // returns all
    
6. Normal DOM vs Shadow DOM
Feature & Normal DOM & Shadow DOM
---------------------------------
- Access -> Direct , Hidden
- CSS scopre -> Global , local
- Isolation -> YES , NO
- Selenium support -> Esay , Tricky

7. Problem in Selenium 😵
👉 Normal locator:
    driver.find_element(By.ID, "username")
❌ Will NOT work inside Shadow DOM

👉 Because:
    - Elements are not visible in main DOM
    - They are encapsulated

8. How to Handle Shadow DOM in Selenium (Important 🔥)
✅ Step-by-step (Using JavaScript)
host = driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "host-element")

shadow_root = driver.execute_script("return arguments[0].shadowRoot", host)

element = shadow_root.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "input")

element.send_keys("Hello")

9. Nested Shadow DOM (Advanced)
👉 Shadow DOM inside another Shadow DOM
host1 = driver.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "parent-host")
shadow1 = driver.execute_script("return arguments[0].shadowRoot", host1)

host2 = shadow1.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "child-host")
shadow2 = driver.execute_script("return arguments[0].shadowRoot", host2)

element = shadow2.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "input")
element.send_keys("Nested")

10. Selenium 4 Shortcut
👉 Direct method available:
shadow_root = host.shadow_root
shadow_root.find_element(By.CSS_SELECTOR, "input").send_keys("Hi")


11. How to Identify Shadow DOM
👉 In Chrome DevTools:
    - Right click -> Inspect
    - Look for:
        #shadow-root(open)
👉 That means Shadow DOM exists

12. Key Interview Points 🎯
- Shadow DOM provides Encapsualtion
- Isolates CSS & Javascript
- Selenium cannot directly access it
- Use:
    - Javascript executor OR
    - shadow_root(Selenium 4)
- Types: Open & Closed

13. Common Mistakes ❌
- Using XPath directly inside a shadow DOM
- Skipping the shadow root
- Trying to access closed shadow DOM

14. When it will fail?
- Closed Shadow DOM:
    - Cannot be accessed vis Selenium
- Solution:
    - Need developer support
    - Or use alternative testing approach

